dc_title_s: Plan of the country bordering the great trunk road between Calcutta and Benares based on the great triangulation and revenue survey operations to 1857
dc_description_s: Shows counties, cities and towns, railroads, and Minnesota state population as of 1880.; "113" at base of Minnesota map and "114" to the left of Missouri map, likely atlas plate numbers.; Probably detached from Loomis T. Palmer's Gaskell's new and complete family atlas of the world, 1886.; Prime meridians: Greenwich and Washington, D.C.; Includes continuation of Cook County, Minnesota, as inset.|81 x 124 centimeters|Scale 1:506,880; 8 miles = 1 inch|General Map Collection
